# Changelog

## 1.0.0 — Initial public release

Multi-provider AI gateway in Go. Highlights:

- One OpenAI-compatible HTTP endpoint that routes to multiple LLM backends
  (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google Gemini, DeepSeek, Groq, Together, OpenRouter,
  local llama.cpp, Cursor, Codex, Antigravity, Kiro, GitHub Copilot, …).
- Subscription auth: drive Claude Code / Cursor / Codex through your
  existing Claude Pro/Max plan (or paid IDE bundles) without an extra
  per-token API key.
- Auto format translation: OpenAI ⇄ Anthropic ⇄ Gemini, including
  streaming SSE and tool-calling.
- Cost-tier routing classifies each request as cheap / standard / strong
  and picks providers by `tier:*` tag — saves money on simple queries.
- Smart RTK token saver with auto-detected tool-output compressors
  (git-diff, build-output, grep, find, tree, ls, dedup-log, smart-truncate).
- Brain endpoint: server-side RAG enrichment + skill injection from a
  Memory Palace SQLite DB. Plug-and-play; off when no DB present.
- Media stack: STT (Deepgram / AssemblyAI / Gemini / Whisper), TTS,
  embeddings, image generation, web fetch + search.
- MITM TLS inspector with per-SNI cert minting, DNS hijack and per-IDE
  rewriters (Antigravity / Copilot / Cursor / Kiro).
- Embedded SPA dashboard with 20 tabs, i18n (en / id / ja-JP / vi / zh-CN),
  provider presets, OAuth import, tunnel watchdog, MCP registry, per-day
  usage analytics, quota tracker (live + cached).
- `flow-cli` companion binary (interactive TUI, autostart, tray).
- Single binary, no CGO, Linux / macOS / Windows.
